   "source": [
    "df = dataset.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill numeric columns\n",
    "for col in df.columns:\n",
    "    if pd.api.types.is_numeric_dtype(df[col]):\n",
    "        df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].median())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill non-numeric (categorical) columns\n",
    "for col in df.columns:\n",
    "    if df[col].dtype == 'object':\n",
    "        df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].mode()[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Now check again\n",
    "df.isnull().sum()"
   ]
  },

   "id": "abab036f-2bd2-4a89-b044-098eff3c5b29",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Axes: ylabel='Eosinophils (%)'>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Eosinophils (%)\n",
    "q1 = df['Eosinophils (%)'].quantile(0.25)\n",
    "q3 = df['Eosinophils (%)'].quantile(0.75)\n",
    "iqr = q3 - q1\n",
    "upper_limit = q3 + 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "lower_limit = q1 - 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "\n",
    "df['Eosinophils (%)'] = np.where(df['Eosinophils (%)'] > upper_limit, upper_limit,\n",
    "                                 np.where(df['Eosinophils (%)'] < lower_limit, lower_limit, df['Eosinophils (%)']))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(df['Eosinophils (%)'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Basophils (%)\n",
    "q1 = df['Basophils (%)'].quantile(0.25)\n",
    "q3 = df['Basophils (%)'].quantile(0.75)\n",
    "iqr = q3 - q1\n",
    "upper_limit = q3 + 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "lower_limit = q1 - 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "\n",
    "df['Basophils (%)'] = np.where(df['Basophils (%)'] > upper_limit, upper_limit,\n",
    "                                np.where(df['Basophils (%)'] < lower_limit, lower_limit, df['Basophils (%)']))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(df['Basophils (%)'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Platelet Count\n",
    "sns.boxplot(df['Platelet Count (lakhs/mm)'])"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Encode categorical features\n",
    "x = pd.get_dummies(x, drop_first=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill NaNs\n",
    "x = x.fillna(x.mean())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Encode y if needed\n",
    "y = y.map({'Yes': 1, 'No': 0})  # Modify based on your actual values\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split again after cleanup\n",
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load your dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_excel(\"HealthCareData.xlsx\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clean up column names\n",
    "df.columns = df.columns.str.strip().str.replace(r\"\\s+\", \" \", regex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define target and features\n",
    "target_col = 'Predicted Value(Out Come-Patient suffering from liver cirrosis or not)'\n",
    "df = df.dropna(subset=[target_col])\n",
    "y = df[target_col]\n",
    "x = df.drop(columns=[target_col])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert categorical features\n",
    "x = pd.get_dummies(x, drop_first=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Handle missing values\n",
    "x = x.fillna(x.mean())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train-test split\n",
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42\n",
    ")"
   ]

    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load your dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_excel(r\"C:\\Users\\kolla\\OneDrive\\Desktop\\flask\\HealthCareData.xlsx\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clean up column names\n",
    "df.columns = df.columns.str.strip().str.replace(r\"\\s+\", \" \", regex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define target and features\n",
    "target_col = 'Predicted Value(Out Come-Patient suffering from liver cirrosis or not)'\n",
    "df = df.dropna(subset=[target_col])\n",
    "y = df[target_col]\n",
    "x = df.drop(columns=[target_col])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert categorical features\n",
    "x = pd.get_dummies(x, drop_first=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Handle missing values\n",
    "x = x.fillna(x.mean())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train-test split\n",
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },

    "import pickle\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "model = RandomForestClassifier()\n",
    "model.fit(x_train, y_train)  # Make sure x_train and y_train are ready\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save it fresh â€” important to use 'wb' (write binary)\n",
    "with open('rf_acc_68.pkl', 'wb') as f:\n",
    "    pickle.dump(model, f)"

    "from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "knn = KNeighborsClassifier()\n",
    "k = np.random.randint(1, 50, 60)\n",
    "params = {'n_neighbors': k}\n",
    "\n",
    "random_search = RandomizedSearchCV(knn, params, n_iter=5, cv=5, n_jobs=-1, verbose=0)\n",
    "random_search.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('train_score -', random_search.score(x_train, y_train))\n",
    "print('test_score  -', random_search.score(x_test, y_test))"
